# Implementation Log — v041-scope-fenced-reviews

## What was implemented

**Scope-fenced reviews** across three gates. Anchor-based mechanical demotion of out-of-domain findings to a non-blocking Observations section. Verdict computation excludes Observations.

- Anchor whitelist per stage (spec / plan / PR), documented in both command docs and `AGENTS.md`
- Anchor parse rule (MUST-001): first `^\[[^\]]+\]` token of `message` cell after leading whitespace
- Three demotion tags: `anchor-out-of-domain`, `no-anchor`, `anchor-requires-spec` (PR-only chore-PR case)
- Preservation invariant: demoted findings keep `severity` / `rule_id` / `location` / `message` / `fix_hint` / source byte-for-byte; `tag` column records demotion reason; severity caps at Info for Verdict computation
- Stage-specific prompts: `Focus (<stage>):` + `Out of scope (<stage>):` + anchor whitelist in every review prompt
- Step 6 report format: `### Observations` section between Cross-source findings and Verdict, with literal "Verdict computation excludes Observations"
- Deterministic regression harness `tests/review-synthesis/drift-demotion.sh` + 4 fixtures

## What existing code was leveraged

- Subagent `allowed-tools: Read, Grep, Glob` allowlist — unchanged
- `codex exec ... -s read-only` dispatch pattern — unchanged
- Stage-then-read `mktemp -d` tempfile — unchanged
- Path gate `pwd -P` canonicalization — unchanged
- Degraded-mode `CLAUDE-PASS: UNAVAILABLE (<reason>)` contract — unchanged
- PR-comment self-identification marker `<!-- ai-driver-review -->` — unchanged
- Existing-reviewer cross-check in review-pr Step 2c (v0.3.4+) — unchanged
- Template-sync CI — unchanged
- Existing table schema `| Severity | rule_id | location | message | fix_hint |` — unchanged

All v0.4.0 surviving defenses verified intact by AC-012 (passive invariant).

## Issues encountered

1. **Em-dash vs colon typo (T004)**: First edit to `review-spec.md` wrote `Focus (spec review) —` (em-dash); AC required `Focus (spec review):` (colon). Fixed via `replace_all` Edit then `--amend` (branch not yet pushed). Per CLAUDE.md preference, a separate fix commit would have been cleaner.

2. **Phase 0 + Phase 1 review skip** (documented `--accept-high` equivalent): re-running Codex Phase 0/1 after 4 external rounds would re-enter the loop this very PR aims to fix. Rationale logged in `spec-review.md` and `tasks.md`. Passive verification ACs (AC-006, AC-012) moved into T010 acceptance run.

3. **No significant implementation blockers**. All 13 ACs passed on the first full acceptance run.

